As of the [[census]]<ref name=census>{{cite web | title = American FactFinder | url = http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4927270 | archive-url = https://archive.today/20200212163352/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4927270 | url-status = dead | archive-date = 12 February 2020 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]] | accessdate = 20 July 2012}}</ref> of 2010, there were 145 people living in the CDP. There were 96 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the CDP was 97.9% White, 0.7% Asian, and 1.4% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 2.1% of the population.

